So, I said that at some point I'd make a post describing what this skip is about and what's going on, here. Insert vague  prologue here:

EXPLANATION:

–block


This skip is about genocide denial.

This idea started way back when I was doing searches on the site and noticed there wasn't a  the result was an article I didn't feel satisfied with (for various reasons). I sat on the premise for a while.

Eventually, I had a new idea. I wanted to invoke the Communism will win) once said about them always stuck with me: the DoA can be a metaphor for how we bury our horrible past so deeply that upon 'rediscovering' it, it looks like it belongs to someone else. This is what I realized I wanted to evoke.

With each revision, the Foundation rediscovers the site  but it keeps coming back. People keep remembering.

I won't tell you what the blacked out text is, but I'll mention some words you might find if you peeked:  instead of documents (to evoke mass sterilization campaigns). There's a reason this takes place in Japan (on Hashima Island, specifically). There's even a reason for the air sirens (connecting it to WW2).

Something so unspeakably horrible happened here that the Foundation has disassociated themselves from it in every way imaginable. This past is so toxic, so destructive, so corrosive that every time they rediscover it, it literally rots their brains until they bury it even deeper only for it to seep through the cracks, and for them to rediscover it again.

SCP-4182 is about the idea of being haunted by a horrible curse, a ghost that you keep insisting isn't real  only to discover that the ghost is your very own.

